<subSubSection id="13B43CBBF010FF9AFCF4D86EFB00FBB3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5B116F30F010FF9AFCF4D86EFB00FBB3" blockId="1.[807,1452,803,1144]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFCF4D86EFC6AFCFA" bold="true" box="[809,929,803,827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="9CAE14B3F010FF9AFC71D86EFBA1FCFA" authorityName="Nijssen &amp; Isbrucker" authorityYear="1987" box="[940,1130,803,827]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Spectracanthicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFC71D86EFBA1FCFA" box="[940,1130,803,827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Spectracanthicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed from all other 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE14B3F010FF9AFCF4D80BFC52FC9F" authorityName="Kner" authorityYear="1853" box="[809,921,838,862]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Ancistrini">Ancistrini</taxonomicName>
, except 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE14B3F010FF9AFC25D80BFB3EFC9C" baseAuthorityName="Castelnau" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[1016,1269,838,861]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Baryancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="niveatus">
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFC25D80BFB3EFC9C" box="[1016,1269,838,861]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Baryancistrus niveatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE14B3F010FF9AFAEFD80BFA6FFC9F" authorityName="Lujan, Arce &amp; Armbruster" authorityYear="2009" box="[1330,1444,838,862]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Baryancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beggini">
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFAEFD80BFA6FFC9F" box="[1330,1444,838,862]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">B. beggini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE14B3F010FF9AFC83D824FC3FFC41" authorityName="Bleeker in Bleeker" authorityYear="1862" box="[862,1012,873,896]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Parancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFC83D824FC3FFC41" box="[862,1012,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Parancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of an expansion of dorsal-fin membrane connecting the last dorsal-fin ray of to the adipose-fin spine (
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFB9AD8E3FBAFFC04" box="[1095,1124,942,965]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">vs.</emphasis>
dorsal fin not expanded and connected to adipose). 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE14B3F010FF9AFBC8D89DFB01FC29" authorityName="Nijssen &amp; Isbrucker" authorityYear="1987" box="[1045,1226,976,1000]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Spectracanthicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFBC8D89DFB01FC29" box="[1045,1226,976,1000]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Spectracanthicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE14B3F010FF9AFCFAD8BEFC71FBCB" box="[807,954,1011,1034]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Baryancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFCFAD8BEFC71FBCB" box="[807,954,1011,1034]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Baryancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having up to 25 teeth on premaxilla (
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFA88D8BEFABAFBCB" box="[1365,1393,1011,1034]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">vs.</emphasis>
more than 25); and from 
<taxonomicName id="9CAE14B3F010FF9AFC30DF5BFBBDFBEC" authorityName="Bleeker in Bleeker" authorityYear="1862" box="[1005,1142,1046,1069]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Parancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFC30DF5BFBBDFBEC" box="[1005,1142,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Parancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having small gill opening, reaching up to 
<superScript id="ACDBC278F010FF9AFC17DF7BFC1AFB85" attach="right" box="[970,977,1078,1092]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1</superScript>
/ 
<subScript id="C72A6D75F010FF9AFC04DF05FC2AFB97" attach="left" box="[985,993,1096,1110]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">3</subScript>
of cleithrum length (
<emphasis id="69DAB322F010FF9AFB18DF75FB29FB8E" box="[1221,1250,1080,1103]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">vs.</emphasis>
large gill opening, reaching nearly 
<superScript id="ACDBC278F010FF9AFC0CDF15FC12FBA7" attach="right" box="[977,985,1112,1126]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1</superScript>
/ 
<subScript id="C72A6D75F010FF9AFC3DDF27FC23FBB9" attach="left" box="[992,1000,1130,1144]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">2</subScript>
of cleithrum length).
</paragraph>
